# ============================================================
# AI Flow - Workspace Management
# ============================================================
# AI Flow creates three directories under .ai-flow/:
#
# 1. .ai-flow/cache/    - Regenerable analysis & test results
#    ├── docs-analysis.json  (costly to regenerate)
#    ├── audit-data.json     (Phase 0 metadata)
#    ├── test-results.json   (test outputs)
#    ├── lint-results.json   (linting outputs)
#    └── type-results.json   (type checking outputs)
#
# 2. .ai-flow/work/     - Temporary WIP state (personal)
#    ├── [task-name]/work.md     (implementation plan)
#    ├── [task-name]/status.json (validation state)
#    └── [task-name]/PAUSED      (pause flag)
#
# 3. .ai-flow/archive/  - Historical metrics (team-shared)
#    └── analytics.jsonl (append-only development metrics)
#
# Default Strategy:
# - Ignore cache/ and work/ (temporary, regenerable)
# - Commit archive/ (non-regenerable team metrics)
#
# Exception for Large Monorepos:
# If docs-analysis.json takes >5 minutes to generate,
# consider committing .ai-flow/cache/docs-analysis.json
# to share analysis across team (add to repo explicitly).
# ============================================================

# Ignore temporary cache (regenerable)
.ai-flow/cache/

# Ignore work-in-progress state (personal, deleted on task completion)
.ai-flow/work/

# COMMIT .ai-flow/archive/ by default (contains team metrics)
# Contains analytics.jsonl with development velocity data